Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Crush the @black peppercorns{1/2%ounce} inside the bag with a #mallet or heavy pan{} until finely crushed. Halve, peel, and mince the @shallot{1}. Peel and cut the @sweet potato{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Place them in a #pot with enough water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil, and cook for ~{10-15%minutes}, until fork-tender. Drain and return to the same #pot.

Toss the @baby broccolini{6%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for about ~{15%minutes}, until slightly crispy.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a 9.5-10-inch #stainless steel pan{} over medium-high heat. Season the @chicken breasts{12%ounce} on all sides with salt. Add to the pan and cook for ~{3-4%minutes} per side, until browned but not yet cooked through. Transfer the chicken to the baking sheet in the oven to finish cooking for about ~{5%minutes}. Let it rest for ~{5%minutes} before serving.

Add the minced shallot to the same pan over medium heat. Cook, tossing for ~{1-2%minutes}, until softened. Add in the @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1%cup}, scraping up the browned bits from the bottom of the pan. Bring to a boil and simmer until thickened and reduced by half. Remove the pan from the heat, then stir in the @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and as much black peppercorn as you like. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Mash the sweet potatoes: Mash the sweet potatoes with a #fork or #potato masher{} until smooth. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and season to taste with salt and pepper. Reheat over medium heat, if necessary.

Serve: Thinly slice the pan-seared chicken and serve alongside the roasted broccolini and mashed sweet potatoes. Drizzle the peppercorn sauce over the dish and enjoy!